				\begin{document}$$_2$$\end{document} dielectric membrane, with near unity emissivity, and long-term operational stability. Processing of the chip is simplified by employing standard CMOS tungsten heaters as micro-reactors for precise in-situ CNT growth, allowing scalable integration at waver level. The same heating elements also serve as enablers for versatile self-annealing thermal profiles that can be adapted for easy optimization of various processes. We show stable operation for alumina-encapsulated CNTs up to recordÂ temperatures of 900 â\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
